totalCaseBoxplotHeaderHTML.html: How to interpret these charts: The bar across the middle of the box gives the median of all states on that date. Half the states fall within the box, a quarter above it and a quarter below it. Dots in a horizontal line near the top of the graph are not real data, but mean there is a data point at that level or higher (if the graph were scaled to show everything, the interesting part of the graph would be all squished at the bottom)

totalCaseHeaderHTML.html:
Trends of total cases

Let's hope total number of total cases curve continues to flatten.

A 7-day moving average often shows trends more clearly.

Without averaging, states which do not report on Sundays, e.g., make the data look less uniform than it is.

vaccHeaderHTML.html:
Vaccinations, People Fully Vaccinated

Vaccination data is shown by percent of state or of US as a whole.

Highest People Fully Vaccinated rate: Montana with 74.6 percent

Next highest rate: Puerto Rico with 63.9 percent

Lowest People Fully Vaccinated rate: Wyoming with 36.8 percent

Next lowest rate: Idaho with 37 percent

Note that 'Total Doses' will be above 100% when close to 50% of the population has had a second dose!
